parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbags did not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a faulty airbag system, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The dealer does not have the parts to repair the recall
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair
and the vehicle owner is unable to get the repair done.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause structural failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also lead to the loss of vehicle control, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The spare tire falls off
the bed of the truck rusts and moves excessively
the rear bumper falls off
the frame cracks or breaks
the rear crossmember rots away
the exhaust system and catalytic converter heat shield fall off
the bed mounting bolts rust off
and the frame rails are split or cracked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unstable and potentially lead to accidents, especially if the corrosion leads to the failure of critical components such as the suspension or steering system.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
especially in the rear section
leading to the failure of components such as the leaf springs
shackles
and brackets. The rust can also cause the spare tire to fall off
and the fuel tank to become unsupported.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of suspension and steering components can cause the vehicle to become unstable and potentially lead to accidents, especially if the failure occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Failure of components such as the wheel bearings
hub assemblies
and ball joints
leading to uneven tire wear
vibrations
and noise while driving. The failure can also cause the vehicle to pull to one side or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of wheels and tires can cause the vehicle to become unstable and potentially lead to accidents, especially if the failure occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Uneven tire wear
tire failure
and wheel damage due to improper alignment
worn-out ball joints
and other suspension component failures.
